4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Rental home marketplaces include online
6 platforms or services such as Vacation Rentals By Owner
7 (VRBO) and Airbnb which connect property owners to
8 short term renters. Existing laws do not provide
9 reimbursement guarantees to rental home marketplace
10 users for damages to property shared through a rental
11 home marketplace.
12 This bill would require rental home marketplaces
13 doing business in this state to maintain a
14 reimbursement insurance policy.
15 This bill would create the Rental Home
16 Marketplace Guarantees Act to define and regulate
17 rental home marketplace guarantees.
18 This bill would provide for oversight of and
19 consumer protections for rental home marketplace
20 guarantees by the Commissioner of Insurance; would give
21 enforcement and rulemaking authority to the
22 Commissioner of Insurance; and would also provide for
23 monetary penalties, hearings, and court proceedings.
24
25
26 A BILL
27 TO BE ENTITLED
28 AN ACT
Page 1

AN ACT
HB296 INTRODUCED
29
30 Relating to consumer protection; to establish the
31 Rental Home Marketplace Guarantees Act; to define and regulate
32 rental home marketplace guarantees; to provide administration,
33 registration, and enforcement duties upon the Commissioner of
34 Insurance; and to provide for financial penalties for
35 violations of the act.
36 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
37 Section 1. This act shall be known and may be cited as
38 the Rental Home Marketplace Guarantees Act.
39 Section 2. As used in this act, the following terms
40 have the following meanings:
41 (1) COMMISSIONER. The Alabama Commissioner of
42 Insurance.
43 (2) PERSON. An individual, partnership, corporation,
44 incorporated or unincorporated association, joint stock
45 company, syndicate, or any similar entity or combination of
46 entities acting in concert.
47 (3) PLATFORM CONTRACT HOLDER. A platform user who is
48 the beneficiary or holder of a rental home marketplace
49 guarantee.
50 (4) PROVIDER. A rental home marketplace doing business
51 in this state or an affiliate or representative of the rental
52 home marketplace that issues, offers, or administers a rental
53 home marketplace guarantee either directly or through a third
54 party.
55 (5) REIMBURSEMENT INSURANCE POLICY. A policy of
56 insurance issued to a provider that states that the insurer
Page 2

insurance issued to a provider that states that the insurer
HB296 INTRODUCED
57 will cover all liabilities and duties under the rental home
58 marketplace guarantee if the provider defaults or fails to
59 perform.
60 (6) RENTAL HOME MARKETPLACE. A person who meets all of
61 the following criteria:
62 a. Provides an online application, software, website,
63 system, or other medium through which a property is advertised
64 or is offered to the public as available in this state and
65 that connects platform users to enable them to share property.
66 b. Provides, directly or indirectly, or maintains an
67 online platform by performing any of the following:
68 1. Transmitting or otherwise communicating the offer or
69 acceptance of a transaction between two platform users.
70 2. Owning or operating the electronic infrastructure or
71 technology that brings two or more platform users together.
72 3. If engaged in the offering of rental home
73 marketplace guarantees, does so only in a manner that is
74 ancillary to the conduct of its primary legitimate business or
75 activity.
76 c. Is not a local or state governmental entity.
77 (7) RENTAL HOME MARKETPLACE GUARANTEE. A contract or
78 agreement issued in connection with a rental home marketplace,
79 whether or not for separate consideration, to reimburse a user
80 sharing property for any damages for which the renter is
81 responsible under the rental home marketplace's terms of
82 service, with or without additional provisions for incidental
83 payment of indemnity for related damages.
84 Section 3. (a) A rental home marketplace guarantee
Page 3

Section 3. (a) A rental home marketplace guarantee
HB296 INTRODUCED
85 shall not be issued or offered in this state unless the
86 provider has made the rental home marketplace guarantee terms
87 available on the provider's website and has complied with this
88 act.
89 (b) No later than March 1, 2027, or prior to commencing
90 offering rental home marketplace guarantees, providers of
91 rental home marketplace guarantees offered in this state shall
92 file a registration with the commissioner on a form and at a
93 fee prescribed by the commissioner. Fees collected pursuant to
94 this section shall be deposited in the State Treasury to the
95 credit of the Insurance Department Fund.
96 (c) No later than July 1, 2027, or prior to commencing
97 offering rental home marketplace guarantees, each provider
98 must obtain and maintain a reimbursement insurance policy
99 issued by an insurer authorized to transact insurance in this
100 state or written pursuant to Chapter 10 of Title 27.
101 Section 4. Rental home marketplace guarantees do not
102 constitute insurance and are not required to comply with any
103 provision of the insurance laws of this state except as
104 provided in this act.
105 Section 5. (a) Reimbursement insurance policies
106 insuring rental home marketplace guarantees offered in this
107 state shall clearly state that, upon default or nonperformance
108 of the provider under the rental home marketplace guarantee,
109 the insurer that issued the policy shall pay on behalf of the
110 provider any sums the provider is obligated to pay according
111 to the rental home marketplace guarantee.
112 (b) A reimbursement insurance policy shall be subject
Page 4

(b) A reimbursement insurance policy shall be subject
HB296 INTRODUCED
113 to the laws and regulations governing termination and
114 nonrenewal of insurance policies in this state. The
115 termination of a reimbursement insurance policy shall not
116 reduce the issuer's responsibility for rental home marketplace
117 guarantees issued by providers before the effective date of
118 the termination.
119 (c) A provider is the agent of the insurer that issued
120 the reimbursement insurance policy. The insurer may seek
121 reimbursement from the provider for any payments made to a
122 platform contract holder which the provider was initially
123 obligated to pay. This act does not prevent or limit that
124 right.
125 Section 6. (a) Rental home marketplace guarantees
126 offered in this state shall include a statement in
127 substantially the following form: "This rental home
128 marketplace guarantee is not an insurance contract."
129 (b) Rental home marketplace guarantees shall contain a
130 statement in substantially the following form: "A
131 reimbursement insurance policy backs obligations of the
132 provider. If the provider is unable or fails to perform on its
133 contractual obligation under a rental home marketplace
134 guarantee within 180 days after proof of loss has been filed,
135 a platform user is entitled to make a claim directly against
136 the insurance company, subject to the terms of the policy."
137 (c) Rental home marketplace guarantees shall be written
138 in clear, understandable language and shall specify the terms,
139 limitations, exceptions, conditions, or exclusions, including
140 conditions governing transferability or termination.
Page 5

conditions governing transferability or termination.
