141 (d) In connection with the offer or advertisement of a
142 rental home marketplace guarantee, a provider shall not make,
143 permit, or cause to be made any false or misleading statement
144 or deliberately omit any material statement that would be
145 considered misleading if omitted.
146 Section 7. (a) The commissioner may conduct
147 investigations of providers or other persons to enforce this
148 act and protect platform contract holders in this state. Upon
149 the commissioner's request, the provider shall make all
150 accounts, books, and records concerning rental home
151 marketplace guarantees sold in this state by the provider
152 available to the commissioner, which are necessary to enable
153 the commissioner to determine compliance or noncompliance with
154 this act.
155 (b) Investigations conducted by the commissioner shall
156 be pursuant to the same examination authority of the
157 commissioner relative to insurers as provided in Chapter 2 of
158 Title 27, Code of Alabama 1975, and investigation expenses
159 shall be processed as examination expenses in accordance with
160 Section 27-2-25, Code of Alabama 1975, which may be presented
161 periodically during the investigation or at the end of the
162 investigation, as the commissioner deems appropriate.
163 (c) The commissioner may take action that is necessary
164 or appropriate to enforce this act and the commissioner's
165 regulations and orders, and to protect platform contract
166 holders in this state.
167 (d) If a provider has violated this act or the
168 commissioner's regulations or orders, the commissioner may
Page 6

commissioner's regulations or orders, the commissioner may
HB296 INTRODUCED
169 issue an order directed to that provider: (i) to cease and
170 desist from committing violations of this act or the
171 commissioner's regulations or orders; (ii) to prohibit the
172 selling or offering for sale rental home marketplace
173 guarantees in violation of this act; (iii) to impose a civil
174 penalty; or (iv) any combination of the foregoing.
175 (e) A provider negatively impacted by an order issued
176 under subsection (d) may request a hearing before the
177 commissioner. The hearing request shall be filed with the
178 commissioner no more than 20 days from the effective date of
179 the commissioner's order.
180 (f) If a hearing is requested, the effective date of
181 the order is automatically suspended until the hearing is
182 complete and the commissioner has reached a final decision.
183 (g) A provider shall have the same rights as insurers
184 to request a hearing in accordance with Article 1 of Chapter 2
185 of Title 27, Code of Alabama 1975, and to appeal as provided
186 in Section 27-2-32, Code of Alabama 1975.
187 (h) The commissioner may bring an action in the Circuit
188 Court of Montgomery County, Alabama, for an injunction or
189 other appropriate relief to enjoin threatened or existing
190 violations of this act or of the commissioner's orders or
191 regulations. An action filed under this section may also seek
192 restitution on behalf of providers negatively impacted by a
193 violation of this act or orders or regulations of the
194 commissioner.
195 (i) A provider who is found to have violated this act
196 may be ordered to pay to the commissioner a civil penalty in
Page 7

may be ordered to pay to the commissioner a civil penalty in
