197 an amount determined by the commissioner of not more than five
198 hundred dollars ($500) per violation and no more than ten
199 thousand dollars ($10,000) in the aggregate for all violations
200 of a similar nature. For purposes of this section, violations
201 shall be of a similar nature if the violation consists of the
202 same or similar course of conduct, action, or practice,
203 regardless of the frequency of the specific act.
204 Section 8. The commissioner may adopt regulations to
205 implement this act.
206 Section 9. This act shall become effective on October
207 1, 2026.
